Package fr.cnrs.iees.io.parsing

Class ValidPropertyTypes

java.lang.Object
fr.cnrs.iees.io.parsing.ValidPropertyTypes
public class ValidPropertyTypes extends Object

This class records the property types which are compatible with a given application using SimplePropertyList implementations. By default it contains only primitive and table types. It is meant to remain a singleton class (ie no instances).

NOTE: to be valid as a property, a class must implement the SaveableAsText interface to save as text, and a static valueOf(String) method performing the reverse operation (instantiating from text). As a consequence, all enum classes are eligible as valid property types since they all have a valueOf(...) method matching their toString() method.

The test case ValidPropertyTypesTest shows all the major use case and expected behaviours.

Author:
Jacques Gignoux - 25-10-2018
